14/11/2006
PRAGUE, Czech Republic -- Croatian President Stipe Mesic called for more Czech investments in his country, as he kicked off a two-day visit to Prague on Monday (November 13th). 
In particular, he noted the investment opportunities offered by the tourism sector. 
Meeting with Czech counterpart Vaclav Klaus, Mesic thanked Prague for its ongoing support of Croatia's EU membership bid. 
(Poslovni dnevnik, Vjesnik - 14/11/06; HINA, HRT - 13/11/06)
